BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:_73Azcu0dJuw0n3iD7h2s
SUMMARY:Trail Explorers - Kelly's Brook Trail
DTSTAMP:20260317T043041Z
DTSTART:20260318T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join the Trail Explorers on Wednesday\, March 18\, at 10:30 a.m
	. They will be exploring Kelly's Brook Trail\, and the meeting location is
	 the Farmer’s Market: 245 Freshwater Road. Upper parking lot. This trail i
	s 4 km and will take approximately 60-75 minutes to complete. It is rated 
	a 3 on the difficulty scale \\(on a 1-5 scale\, with 1 being the easiest a
	nd 5 being the hardest. For more information please visit: https://www.stj
	ohns.ca/en/recreation-culture/trail-explorers.aspx This initiative provide
	s a wonderful opportunity to explore the beautiful trails throughout the c
	ity\, promoting health\, wellness\, and community connection. Please conta
	ct healthyprograms@stjohns.ca for further information.\n\nhttps://seatoday
	.6amcity.com/events/#/details/trail-explorers-kelly-s-brook-trail/18083541
	/2026-03-18T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/trail-explorers-kelly-s-b
	rook-trail/18083541/2026-03-18T00
LOCATION:Farmer's Market: 245 Freshwater Road. Upper parking lot\, 4749 Bal
	lard Ave NW\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:xwaI4cPwH6EtB3uQ6zG_o
SUMMARY:Audubon Bird Walk
DTSTAMP:20260317T043041Z
DTSTART:20260319T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:Learn more about the birds at the Bellevue Botanical Garden. Jo
	in Eastside Audubon for a monthly walk that explores the birds and their h
	abitat in the Garden. This one-mile walk will be on trails with various su
	rfaces and may include gravel\, mulch\, or pavement. Please dress for the 
	weather and wear comfortable walking shoes. Parking in the lot is free. Fr
	om the parking lot enter the garden through the breezeway and turn left. M
	eet your guide in the covered Gathering Place. This walk is for any level 
	of birder and no experience is necessary. Bring binoculars if you have the
	m. There will be some available to loan for the walk. Each walk is $5 per 
	person. Registration is required.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#
	/details/audubon-bird-walk/15998889/2026-03-19T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/audubon-bird-walk/1599888
	9/2026-03-19T00
LOCATION:Bellevue Botanical Garden\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
